cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with mapping and translating clinical jargons to consumer language, which involves natural language processing and computational linguistics.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper utilizes embedding alignment method, which is a machine learning technique.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the quality of the alignment through similar words retrieval.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper involves using machine learning techniques to improve patient-clinician communication.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with improving communication between patients and clinicians, which has societal implications.
